IF EXISTS ( SELECT * FROM sys.external_tables WHERE object_id = OBJECT_ID('dbo.D_STOpsRoute') )
    DROP EXTERNAL TABLE dbo.D_STOpsRoute
GO

CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE dbo.D_STOpsRoute (
    [tms_parentroute_id] bigint,
    [tms_parentroute_name] nvarchar(4000),
    [tms_parentroute_slug] nvarchar(4000),
    [tms_parentroute_parentroute] bigint,
    [tms_parentroute_insdate] datetime2(7),
    [tms_parentroute_moddate] datetime2(7),
    [tms_parentroute_insby] bigint,
    [tms_parentroute_status] nvarchar(4000),
    [tms_parentroute_crossborder] int,
    [tms_parentroute_roundtripdays] int,
    [tms_parentroute_distance] int,
    [tms_parentroute_duration] int,
    [tms_parentroute_numofuse] int,
    [tms_parentroute_legacyid] int,
    [tms_parentroute_local] int


	)
	WITH (
	LOCATION = 'Structured Data/OPS/stopsroute.parquet',
	DATA_SOURCE = [synapse_citylogisticsstorage_dfs_core_windows_net],
	FILE_FORMAT = [SynapseParquetFormat]
	)
GO


SELECT TOP 100 * FROM dbo.D_STOpsRoute 
GO
